Package au.csiro.pathling.fhirpath.collection

Class ResolvedReferenceCollection

java.lang.Object
au.csiro.pathling.fhirpath.collection.Collection
au.csiro.pathling.fhirpath.collection.ResolvedReferenceCollection
All Implemented Interfaces:
Equatable
public class ResolvedReferenceCollection extends Collection
Represents a collection of resolved references that expose type information only.

This collection is returned by the limited resolve() function and supports type checking via the is operator, but does not allow traversal to child elements. Any attempt to traverse will result in an UnsupportedFhirPathFeatureError.

Author:
Piotr Szul

      Builds a new ResolvedReferenceCollection from a column representation and FHIR type.

      The column should contain a value (typically a literal) that indicates the presence of a resolved reference. Null values in the column indicate that the reference could not be resolved.

    • build

      @Nonnull public static ResolvedReferenceCollection build(@Nonnull ColumnRepresentation column)
      Builds a new ResolvedReferenceCollection from a column representation where the type is encoded in the column itself.

      The column should contain the string representation of the FHIR type (e.g., "Patient", "Organization"), or null if the reference could not be resolved.

      Parameters:
      column - the column representation containing type strings
      Returns:
      a new ResolvedReferenceCollection with dynamic type information

      @Nonnull public Collection filterByType(@Nonnull TypeSpecifier type)
      Filters this collection to only include elements of the specified type.

      This method supports type checking with the is operator. If the resolved reference's type matches the specified type, this collection is returned; otherwise, an empty collection is returned.
